<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Simon: The beastmaster will not give a reward when you bring a monster corpse that has the same name as the one expected but is internally different in the code. <p>
Novice warriors for example exist in both loner and group varieties. Other examples exist in the forum. 
</p>
<p>
Renaming one of them only makes certain that some other monster is or will be a duplicate (you can't control the module makers, you know). 
</p>
<p>
3 possible fixes: 
</p>
<p>
-Allow identically named monsters to be acceptable to the beastmaster. 
</p>
<p>
-The beastmaster could avoid duplicate name quests entirely. 
</p>
<p>
-Produce a compiler/link error for identically named monsters, so that this error can no longer be introduced in ToME by mods (you can't control their duplicate-name sloppiness if they manage to compile!). 
</p>
<hr size="3">
  <a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Known, won't be fixed before ToME 3, where I've already told the illustrious maintainer what we need to fix it. <p>
Well, if someone sent me a patch that added name-checking logic to the Beastmaster quest, I'm sure I'd apply it.  However, the real fix is in ToME 3: allowing monsters to be *optionally* generated in groups, controlled by lua. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: Clever! 
</p>
